Q) Write a Python program to create a Pandas DataFrame, add a new column, and display basic statistics.


import pandas as pd

data = {'Name': ['Sohan', 'Raghav', 'Tejas', 'Abeer', 'Shyra'],
                'Age': [25, 30, 35, 40, 28],
                'Salary': [50000, 60000, 70000, 80000, 55000]}

df =  pd.DataFrame(data)

df['Bonus'] = df ['Salary'] * 0.1

print("DataFrame: \n", df)
print("\nStatistics:\n", df.describe())


